  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 13 high, 10 medium, 16 normal. Key bases needing attention include Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 10 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Tuzla (TZL/LQTZ), Varna (VAR/LBWN) and Sofia (SOF/LBSF). Network hotspots: Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG). Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 3 airports changed status, led by Paris-Orly (ORY/LFPO), EuroAirport Basel–Mulhouse–Freiburg (BSL/LFSB), Falcone–Borsellino (PMO/LICJ).",
